f=AI & Agents/forge/operational/commands/forge-commands.md · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\| "which model for", "technique inventory", "cost quality frontier", "routing rec", "what are we running" \| model-technique-registry \| /frontier \| · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\| "benchmark models", "compare X and Y", "blind test", "re-benchmark" \| benchmarking-discipline \| /bench \| · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\| "adopt this technique", "should we switch to", "new method", "paper claims" \| technique-adoption \| /adopt \| · h1:forge — Command Triggers=\| "why is X degrading", "diagnose", "case from gauge", "reopened case" \| degradation-diagnosis \| /diagnose \| · h2:Precedence=open degradation case outranks everything (diagnosis first). "Should switch?" runs technique-adoption, which CALLS benchmarking-discipline never bench hoc outside adoption gate. Registry questions answer recorded facts only; unmeasured entries named such, never estimated.